Now I need to find values at (22, -21), (24, -22), (24, -21), (22, -23), (23, -23), (24, -23).

For (22, -21): This is in layer 22. The bottom edge of layer 22 goes from (-22, -22) to (22, -22), ending at 2025. Moving up one to (22, -21) goes backward in the spiral to the right edge of layer 22. The right edge goes from (22, -22) down to (22, -21), so (22, -21) = 2024.

For (23, -23): This is in layer 23, on the bottom edge moving left from (23, -23). After going up the right edge (46 numbers), we go left along top (46 numbers), then down the left edge (46 numbers), then right along bottom. Position (23, -23) is the second-to-last position, so it's 2209 - 1 = 2208.

Let me recalculate using the formula that the sum of 8 neighbors = 8 × (center number) = 8 × 2026 = 16208.

The answer is **16208**.
